$waterfall_1 = array(
   'title'=>'Description',
   'data'=>'<p>Greenberg & Fitchett (2001) describe a set of user interface software APIs that map to physical
hardware. This technology, named phidgets, is intended to be easy to use so that designers can
build prototypes without requiring the education of an engineer. For our final project, we were
tasked to use some of these phidgets to build a technology.</p>
<p>For my project, I built a Waterfall harp that plays musical chords as the water is \'strummed\'.
I used a commercial appliance that circulated water to make a continuous waterfall. In its
base were backlights. I added three light sensors at its top and used clay to funnel water so
that each sensor had a water rivulet beneath it. I programmed the backend software so that a
musical chord would play whenever a light sensor was blocked for a small time duration. Thus,
as people \'strummed\' the water by moving their fingers through the rivulets and blocking the
sensors, musical chords corresponding to each rivulet would play.</p>
    ',
   'images'=>array(
     '1'=>'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bMc38Nb57Fc'
   )
);

